main event: Two objects were observed moving at high speed in the sky over Mansfield, Ohio on February 15, 1959.
interesting points: The objects were seen from a laboratory window by a witness who estimated they were around 5,000 feet high., The observation lasted for 1 minute and 30 seconds., The witness noted that the objects appeared under a cirrostratus cloud., This was the second time the witness saw a similar type of object that day., The report was concluded as a valid sighting by Project Blue Book.
sighted object: two unidentified flying objects or lights
witness description: A laboratory worker who observed the objects through a window.
